{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":560,"text":"Whether you like it or not,"},{"time":1920,"text":"radical transparency and algorithmic\ndecision-making is coming at you fast,"},{"time":7320,"text":"and it's going to change your life."},{"time":9320,"text":"That's because it's now easy\nto take algorithms"},{"time":12160,"text":"and embed them into computers"},{"time":14080,"text":"and gather all that data\nthat you're leaving on yourself"},{"time":17040,"text":"all over the place,"},{"time":18440,"text":"and know what you're like,"},{"time":20160,"text":"and then direct the computers\nto interact with you"},{"time":23120,"text":"in ways that are better\nthan most people can."}]},{"cues":[{"time":26160,"text":"Well, that might sound scary."},{"time":27800,"text":"I've been doing this for a long time\nand I have found it to be wonderful."},{"time":32159,"text":"My objective has been\nto have meaningful work"},{"time":34840,"text":"and meaningful relationships\nwith the people I work with,"},{"time":37720,"text":"and I've learned that I couldn't have that"},{"time":39800,"text":"unless I had that radical transparency\nand that algorithmic decision-making."},{"time":44680,"text":"I want to show you why that is,"},{"time":46720,"text":"I want to show you how it works."},{"time":48440,"text":"And I warn you that some of the things\nthat I'm going to show you"},{"time":51560,"text":"probably are a little bit shocking."}]},{"cues":[{"time":53760,"text":"Since I was a kid,\nI've had a terrible rote memory."},{"time":58120,"text":"And I didn't like following instructions,"},{"time":60320,"text":"I was no good at following instructions."},{"time":62760,"text":"But I loved to figure out\nhow things worked for myself."},{"time":66680,"text":"When I was 12,"},{"time":68080,"text":"I hated school but I fell in love\nwith trading the markets."},{"time":71920,"text":"I caddied at the time,"},{"time":73600,"text":"earned about five dollars a bag."},{"time":75200,"text":"And I took my caddying money,\nand I put it in the stock market."},{"time":79240,"text":"And that was just because\nthe stock market was hot at the time."},{"time":82640,"text":"And the first company I bought"},{"time":84120,"text":"was a company by the name\nof Northeast Airlines."},{"time":87360,"text":"Northeast Airlines was\nthe only company I heard of"},{"time":90120,"text":"that was selling for less\nthan five dollars a share."}]},{"cues":[{"time":92840,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":94840,"text":"And I figured I could buy more shares,"},{"time":96720,"text":"and if it went up, I'd make more money."},{"time":98840,"text":"So, it was a dumb strategy, right?"},{"time":102360,"text":"But I tripled my money,"},{"time":103840,"text":"and I tripled my money\nbecause I got lucky."},{"time":106520,"text":"The company was about to go bankrupt,"},{"time":108360,"text":"but some other company acquired it,"},{"time":110480,"text":"and I tripled my money."},{"time":111960,"text":"And I was hooked."},{"time":113720,"text":"And I thought, \"This game is easy.\""},{"time":117200,"text":"With time,"},{"time":118440,"text":"I learned this game is anything but easy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":120880,"text":"In order to be an effective investor,"},{"time":123040,"text":"one has to bet against the consensus"},{"time":125960,"text":"and be right."},{"time":127240,"text":"And it's not easy to bet\nagainst the consensus and be right."},{"time":130120,"text":"One has to bet against\nthe consensus and be right"},{"time":132480,"text":"because the consensus\nis built into the price."},{"time":136120,"text":"And in order to be an entrepreneur,"},{"time":138600,"text":"a successful entrepreneur,"},{"time":140240,"text":"one has to bet against\nthe consensus and be right."},{"time":145400,"text":"I had to be an entrepreneur\nand an investor --"},{"time":148360,"text":"and what goes along with that\nis making a lot of painful mistakes."},{"time":153440,"text":"So I made a lot of painful mistakes,"},{"time":156280,"text":"and with time,"},{"time":157560,"text":"my attitude about those mistakes\nbegan to change."},{"time":161160,"text":"I began to think of them as puzzles."},{"time":163280,"text":"That if I could solve the puzzles,"},{"time":165240,"text":"they would give me gems."},{"time":167160,"text":"And the puzzles were:"},{"time":168840,"text":"What would I do differently in the future\nso I wouldn't make that painful mistake?"},{"time":173280,"text":"And the gems were principles"},{"time":175880,"text":"that I would then write down\nso I would remember them"},{"time":179040,"text":"that would help me in the future."},{"time":181000,"text":"And because I wrote them down so clearly,"},{"time":183720,"text":"I could then --"},{"time":185080,"text":"eventually discovered --"},{"time":186680,"text":"I could then embed them into algorithms."},{"time":191400,"text":"And those algorithms\nwould be embedded in computers,"},{"time":194880,"text":"and the computers would\nmake decisions along with me;"},{"time":198240,"text":"and so in parallel,\nwe would make these decisions."},{"time":201400,"text":"And I could see how those decisions\nthen compared with my own decisions,"},{"time":205400,"text":"and I could see that\nthose decisions were a lot better."},{"time":208520,"text":"And that was because the computer\ncould make decisions much faster,"},{"time":213280,"text":"it could process a lot more information"},{"time":215560,"text":"and it can process decisions much more --"},{"time":219880,"text":"less emotionally."},{"time":222760,"text":"So it radically improved\nmy decision-making."}]},{"cues":[{"time":228440,"text":"Eight years after I started Bridgewater,"},{"time":233360,"text":"I had my greatest failure,"},{"time":234920,"text":"my greatest mistake."},{"time":237680,"text":"It was late 1970s,"},{"time":239840,"text":"I was 34 years old,"},{"time":241840,"text":"and I had calculated that American banks"},{"time":245520,"text":"had lent much more money\nto emerging countries"},{"time":248400,"text":"than those countries\nwere going to be able to pay back"},{"time":251240,"text":"and that we would have\nthe greatest debt crisis"},{"time":253960,"text":"since the Great Depression."},{"time":256200,"text":"And with it, an economic crisis"},{"time":258440,"text":"and a big bear market in stocks."},{"time":261680,"text":"It was a controversial view at the time."},{"time":264160,"text":"People thought it was\nkind of a crazy point of view."},{"time":267480,"text":"But in August 1982,"},{"time":269720,"text":"Mexico defaulted on its debt,"},{"time":272520,"text":"and a number of other countries followed."},{"time":274800,"text":"And we had the greatest debt crisis\nsince the Great Depression."},{"time":279080,"text":"And because I had anticipated that,"},{"time":281880,"text":"I was asked to testify to Congress\nand appear on \"Wall Street Week,\""},{"time":286240,"text":"which was the show of the time."},{"time":288240,"text":"Just to give you a flavor of that,\nI've got a clip here,"},{"time":291200,"text":"and you'll see me in there."}]},{"cues":[{"time":294480,"text":"(Video) Mr. Chairman, Mr. Mitchell,"},{"time":296200,"text":"it's a great pleasure and a great honor\nto be able to appear before you"},{"time":299600,"text":"in examination with what\nis going wrong with our economy."},{"time":303640,"text":"The economy is now flat --"},{"time":305600,"text":"teetering on the brink of failure."}]},{"cues":[{"time":307760,"text":"Martin Zweig: You were recently\nquoted in an article."},{"time":310280,"text":"You said, \"I can say this\nwith absolute certainty"},{"time":312640,"text":"because I know how markets work.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":314280,"text":"Ray Dalio: I can say\nwith absolute certainty"},{"time":316400,"text":"that if you look at the liquidity base"},{"time":318280,"text":"in the corporations\nand the world as a whole,"},{"time":321680,"text":"that there's such reduced\nlevel of liquidity"},{"time":323800,"text":"that you can't return\nto an era of stagflation.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":327040,"text":"I look at that now, I think,\n\"What an arrogant jerk!\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":330160,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":333760,"text":"I was so arrogant, and I was so wrong."},{"time":336240,"text":"I mean, while the debt crisis happened,"},{"time":338840,"text":"the stock market and the economy\nwent up rather than going down,"},{"time":342840,"text":"and I lost so much money\nfor myself and for my clients"},{"time":347880,"text":"that I had to shut down\nmy operation pretty much,"},{"time":351320,"text":"I had to let almost everybody go."},{"time":353640,"text":"And these were like extended family,"},{"time":355400,"text":"I was heartbroken."},{"time":357040,"text":"And I had lost so much money"},{"time":358880,"text":"that I had to borrow\n4,000 dollars from my dad"},{"time":362240,"text":"to help to pay my family bills."}]},{"cues":[{"time":364840,"text":"It was one of the most painful\nexperiences of my life ..."},{"time":369240,"text":"but it turned out to be\none of the greatest experiences of my life"},{"time":373040,"text":"because it changed my attitude\nabout decision-making."},{"time":376360,"text":"Rather than thinking, \"I'm right,\""},{"time":379440,"text":"I started to ask myself,"},{"time":381040,"text":"\"How do I know I'm right?\""},{"time":384480,"text":"I gained a humility that I needed"},{"time":386440,"text":"in order to balance my audacity."},{"time":389880,"text":"I wanted to find the smartest\npeople who would disagree with me"},{"time":394120,"text":"to try to understand their perspective"},{"time":396040,"text":"or to have them\nstress test my perspective."},{"time":399400,"text":"I wanted to make an idea meritocracy."},{"time":402200,"text":"In other words,"},{"time":403440,"text":"not an autocracy in which\nI would lead and others would follow"},{"time":407280,"text":"and not a democracy in which everybody's\npoints of view were equally valued,"},{"time":410920,"text":"but I wanted to have an idea meritocracy\nin which the best ideas would win out."},{"time":416040,"text":"And in order to do that,"},{"time":417320,"text":"I realized that we would need\nradical truthfulness"},{"time":420920,"text":"and radical transparency."}]},{"cues":[{"time":422560,"text":"What I mean by radical truthfulness\nand radical transparency"},{"time":426440,"text":"is people needed to say\nwhat they really believed"},{"time":429120,"text":"and to see everything."},{"time":431480,"text":"And we literally\ntape almost all conversations"},{"time":435440,"text":"and let everybody see everything,"},{"time":437080,"text":"because if we didn't do that,"},{"time":438520,"text":"we couldn't really have\nan idea meritocracy."},{"time":442760,"text":"In order to have an idea meritocracy,"},{"time":446480,"text":"we have let people speak\nand say what they want."},{"time":448880,"text":"Just to give you an example,"},{"time":450280,"text":"this is an email from Jim Haskel --"},{"time":453000,"text":"somebody who works for me --"},{"time":454400,"text":"and this was available\nto everybody in the company."},{"time":457800,"text":"\"Ray, you deserve a 'D-'"},{"time":460360,"text":"for your performance\ntoday in the meeting ..."},{"time":462640,"text":"you did not prepare at all well"},{"time":464360,"text":"because there is no way\nyou could have been that disorganized.\""},{"time":469520,"text":"Isn't that great?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":470760,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":472000,"text":"That's great."},{"time":473240,"text":"It's great because, first of all,\nI needed feedback like that."},{"time":476200,"text":"I need feedback like that."},{"time":477840,"text":"And it's great because if I don't let Jim,\nand people like Jim,"},{"time":481320,"text":"to express their points of view,"},{"time":482920,"text":"our relationship wouldn't be the same."},{"time":485000,"text":"And if I didn't make that public\nfor everybody to see,"},{"time":488080,"text":"we wouldn't have an idea meritocracy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":491760,"text":"So for that last 25 years\nthat's how we've been operating."},{"time":495640,"text":"We've been operating\nwith this radical transparency"},{"time":498720,"text":"and then collecting these principles,"},{"time":501040,"text":"largely from making mistakes,"},{"time":503120,"text":"and then embedding\nthose principles into algorithms."},{"time":507560,"text":"And then those algorithms provide --"},{"time":510280,"text":"we're following the algorithms"},{"time":512320,"text":"in parallel with our thinking."},{"time":515280,"text":"That has been how we've run\nthe investment business,"},{"time":518480,"text":"and it's how we also deal\nwith the people management."}]},{"cues":[{"time":521240,"text":"In order to give you a glimmer\ninto what this looks like,"},{"time":525000,"text":"I'd like to take you into a meeting"},{"time":527360,"text":"and introduce you to a tool of ours\ncalled the \"Dot Collector\""},{"time":530520,"text":"that helps us do this."},{"time":535640,"text":"A week after the US election,"},{"time":537840,"text":"our research team held a meeting"},{"time":539960,"text":"to discuss what a Trump presidency\nwould mean for the US economy."},{"time":544000,"text":"Naturally, people had\ndifferent opinions on the matter"},{"time":546880,"text":"and how we were\napproaching the discussion."},{"time":549840,"text":"The \"Dot Collector\" collects these views."},{"time":552640,"text":"It has a list of a few dozen attributes,"},{"time":554960,"text":"so whenever somebody thinks something\nabout another person's thinking,"},{"time":559000,"text":"it's easy for them\nto convey their assessment;"},{"time":561960,"text":"they simply note the attribute\nand provide a rating from one to 10."},{"time":567520,"text":"For example, as the meeting began,"},{"time":569800,"text":"a researcher named Jen rated me a three --"},{"time":573640,"text":"in other words, badly --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":575680,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":577080,"text":"for not showing a good balance\nof open-mindedness and assertiveness."},{"time":582080,"text":"As the meeting transpired,"},{"time":583560,"text":"Jen's assessments of people\nadded up like this."},{"time":587920,"text":"Others in the room\nhave different opinions."},{"time":590120,"text":"That's normal."},{"time":591360,"text":"Different people are always\ngoing to have different opinions."},{"time":594800,"text":"And who knows who's right?"},{"time":597240,"text":"Let's look at just what people thought\nabout how I was doing."},{"time":601600,"text":"Some people thought I did well,"},{"time":603840,"text":"others, poorly."},{"time":606080,"text":"With each of these views,"},{"time":607440,"text":"we can explore the thinking\nbehind the numbers."},{"time":610520,"text":"Here's what Jen and Larry said."},{"time":613760,"text":"Note that everyone\ngets to express their thinking,"},{"time":616400,"text":"including their critical thinking,"},{"time":618080,"text":"regardless of their position\nin the company."},{"time":621120,"text":"Jen, who's 24 years old\nand right out of college,"},{"time":624240,"text":"can tell me, the CEO,\nthat I'm approaching things terribly."}]},{"cues":[{"time":628480,"text":"This tool helps people\nboth express their opinions"},{"time":632280,"text":"and then separate themselves\nfrom their opinions"},{"time":635400,"text":"to see things from a higher level."},{"time":638640,"text":"When Jen and others shift their attentions\nfrom inputting their own opinions"},{"time":643560,"text":"to looking down on the whole screen,"},{"time":646160,"text":"their perspective changes."},{"time":648680,"text":"They see their own opinions\nas just one of many"},{"time":651840,"text":"and naturally start asking themselves,"},{"time":654400,"text":"\"How do I know my opinion is right?\""},{"time":657480,"text":"That shift in perspective is like going\nfrom seeing in one dimension"},{"time":661560,"text":"to seeing in multiple dimensions."},{"time":663840,"text":"And it shifts the conversation\nfrom arguing over our opinions"},{"time":667960,"text":"to figuring out objective criteria\nfor determining which opinions are best."}]},{"cues":[{"time":672920,"text":"Behind the \"Dot Collector\"\nis a computer that is watching."},{"time":677120,"text":"It watches what all\nthese people are thinking"},{"time":679320,"text":"and it correlates that\nwith how they think."},{"time":681920,"text":"And it communicates advice\nback to each of them based on that."},{"time":686520,"text":"Then it draws the data\nfrom all the meetings"},{"time":689960,"text":"to create a pointilist painting\nof what people are like"},{"time":693200,"text":"and how they think."},{"time":695160,"text":"And it does that guided by algorithms."},{"time":698800,"text":"Knowing what people are like helps\nto match them better with their jobs."},{"time":703120,"text":"For example,"},{"time":704360,"text":"a creative thinker who is unreliable"},{"time":706120,"text":"might be matched up with someone\nwho's reliable but not creative."},{"time":710280,"text":"Knowing what people are like\nalso allows us to decide"},{"time":713640,"text":"what responsibilities to give them"},{"time":715920,"text":"and to weigh our decisions\nbased on people's merits."},{"time":720040,"text":"We call it their believability."},{"time":722560,"text":"Here's an example of a vote that we took"},{"time":724560,"text":"where the majority\nof people felt one way ..."},{"time":728920,"text":"but when we weighed the views\nbased on people's merits,"},{"time":731880,"text":"the answer was completely different."},{"time":734920,"text":"This process allows us to make decisions\nnot based on democracy,"},{"time":739520,"text":"not based on autocracy,"},{"time":741680,"text":"but based on algorithms that take\npeople's believability into consideration."}]},{"cues":[{"time":749520,"text":"Yup, we really do this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":751240,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":754560,"text":"We do it because it eliminates"},{"time":757440,"text":"what I believe to be\none of the greatest tragedies of mankind,"},{"time":761920,"text":"and that is people arrogantly,"},{"time":764760,"text":"naïvely holding opinions\nin their minds that are wrong,"},{"time":769240,"text":"and acting on them,"},{"time":770520,"text":"and not putting them out there\nto stress test them."},{"time":774000,"text":"And that's a tragedy."},{"time":775360,"text":"And we do it because it elevates ourselves\nabove our own opinions"},{"time":780800,"text":"so that we start to see things\nthrough everybody's eyes,"},{"time":783720,"text":"and we see things collectively."},{"time":786360,"text":"Collective decision-making is so much\nbetter than individual decision-making"},{"time":790720,"text":"if it's done well."},{"time":792360,"text":"It's been the secret sauce\nbehind our success."},{"time":795000,"text":"It's why we've made\nmore money for our clients"},{"time":797200,"text":"than any other hedge fund in existence"},{"time":799160,"text":"and made money\n23 out of the last 26 years."}]},{"cues":[{"time":803880,"text":"So what's the problem\nwith being radically truthful"},{"time":808440,"text":"and radically transparent with each other?"},{"time":813400,"text":"People say it's emotionally difficult."},{"time":816240,"text":"Critics say it's a formula\nfor a brutal work environment."},{"time":821400,"text":"Neuroscientists tell me it has to do\nwith how are brains are prewired."},{"time":826280,"text":"There's a part of our brain\nthat would like to know our mistakes"},{"time":829520,"text":"and like to look at our weaknesses\nso we could do better."},{"time":834120,"text":"I'm told that that's\nthe prefrontal cortex."},{"time":837040,"text":"And then there's a part of our brain\nwhich views all of this as attacks."},{"time":841920,"text":"I'm told that that's the amygdala."},{"time":844440,"text":"In other words,\nthere are two you's inside you:"},{"time":847520,"text":"there's an emotional you"},{"time":848960,"text":"and there's an intellectual you,"},{"time":850760,"text":"and often they're at odds,"},{"time":852560,"text":"and often they work against you."},{"time":855160,"text":"It's been our experience\nthat we can win this battle."},{"time":858920,"text":"We win it as a group."},{"time":861000,"text":"It takes about 18 months typically"},{"time":863360,"text":"to find that most people\nprefer operating this way,"},{"time":866440,"text":"with this radical transparency"},{"time":868480,"text":"than to be operating\nin a more opaque environment."},{"time":871840,"text":"There's not politics,\nthere's not the brutality of --"},{"time":876160,"text":"you know, all of that hidden,\nbehind-the-scenes --"},{"time":878560,"text":"there's an idea meritocracy\nwhere people can speak up."},{"time":881520,"text":"And that's been great."},{"time":882800,"text":"It's given us more effective work,"},{"time":884480,"text":"and it's given us\nmore effective relationships."},{"time":887400,"text":"But it's not for everybody."},{"time":889680,"text":"We found something like\n25 or 30 percent of the population"},{"time":892640,"text":"it's just not for."},{"time":894400,"text":"And by the way,"},{"time":895640,"text":"when I say radical transparency,"},{"time":897480,"text":"I'm not saying transparency\nabout everything."},{"time":899840,"text":"I mean, you don't have to tell somebody\nthat their bald spot is growing"},{"time":903680,"text":"or their baby's ugly."},{"time":905320,"text":"So, I'm just talking about --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":907440,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":908680,"text":"talking about the important things."},{"time":910880,"text":"So --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":912120,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":916600,"text":"So when you leave this room,"},{"time":918040,"text":"I'd like you to observe yourself\nin conversations with others."},{"time":923360,"text":"Imagine if you knew\nwhat they were really thinking,"},{"time":927760,"text":"and imagine if you knew\nwhat they were really like ..."},{"time":931840,"text":"and imagine if they knew\nwhat you were really thinking"},{"time":935840,"text":"and what were really like."},{"time":938160,"text":"It would certainly clear things up a lot"},{"time":940760,"text":"and make your operations\ntogether more effective."},{"time":943640,"text":"I think it will improve\nyour relationships."},{"time":946600,"text":"Now imagine that you can have algorithms"},{"time":949920,"text":"that will help you gather\nall of that information"},{"time":953760,"text":"and even help you make decisions\nin an idea-meritocratic way."},{"time":960640,"text":"This sort of radical transparency\nis coming at you"},{"time":965000,"text":"and it is going to affect your life."},{"time":967600,"text":"And in my opinion,"},{"time":969680,"text":"it's going to be wonderful."},{"time":971040,"text":"So I hope it is as wonderful for you"},{"time":973400,"text":"as it is for me."}]},{"cues":[{"time":975160,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":976440,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}